ent)  || ||  12 September 2014  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Greenland}} ||  || [[Ane Lone Bagger]]  || ||  5 October 2018  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Guernsey}} ||  || [[Jonathan Le Tocq]] || ||  6 May 2016  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Jersey}} ||  || [[Ian Gorst]] || ||  7 June 2018  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|New Caledonia}} ||  || [[Thierry Santa]] (President of the Government)  || || 9 July 2019  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Puerto Rico}} ||  || [[Elmer Rom\u00e1n]] || || 20 December 2019  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Tokelau}} ||  || [[Fofo Tuisano]] (prime minister)  || || 9 March 2020  \t\n|-\n|}\n\n== Autonomous administrative divisions ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n! bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\" | Autonomous region\n! bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\" | Historical list of foreign ministers\n! bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\" | Current foreign minister\n! bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\" | Party\n! bgcolor=\"#dddddd\" | Assumed office\n|-\n| {{flag|Brussels-Capital Region}} ||  || [[Pascal Smet]]  || ||  20 July 2019  \t\n|- \t\n| {{flag|Catalonia}} ||  || [[Bernat Sol\u00e9]]  ||  || 21 March 2020  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Flanders}} ||  || [[Jan Jambon]] (Minister-President) || ||  2 October 2019  \t\n|-\n| [[File:Flag_of_Gagauzia.svg|20px]] [[Gagauzia]] ||  || Vitaliy Vlah  || ||  30 April 2015  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Kurdistan}} ||  || [[Safeen Muhsin Dizayee]]  || ||  July 2019  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Quebec}} ||  || [[Nadine Girault]]  || ||  18 October 2018  \t\n|-\n| {{flag|Scotland}} || [[Cabinet Secretary for Culture and External Affairs|List]]  || [[Fiona Hyslop]] || [[Scottish National Party]] ||  1 December 2009  \t\n|-\n| {{BE-WAL}} ||  || [[Elio Di Rupo]] (Minister-President) || ||   13 September 2019\n|- \t\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[:Category:Lists of foreign ministers by year]] \t\n*[[Lists of office-holders]] \t\n*[[List of foreign ministers in {{Currentyear}}]]\n*[[List of current presidents of assembly]] \t\n*[[List of current heads of state and government]] \t\n*[[List of current permanent representatives to the United Nations]] \t\n*[[List of female foreign min